  <h2>Watering your succulent</h2>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col col-lg-9">

      <p>Succulents are named succulents for a reason. They tend to look plump and soft. That's because they like holding on to water! It's actually very easy to take care of succulent watering.
      I call it the forget and remember watering method. The method consists of just forgetting about watering your plant until you remember. They're super resillient so this is fine for them.
      If you want something a little more exact, in summer months, water your succulent every 1-2 weeks and in winter months, water them every 1.5-2.5 weeks.</p>
      <p>Succulents grow best when they have phases of drenches and droughts. You must allow the succulent's soil to completely dry before you water them or you risk overwatering. It's actually very rare
      to underwater your succulent.</p>
      <p>Watering is one of the key items to be concerned about when your planter doesn't have drainage holes. You absolutely do not want the roots to remained soaked otherwise they will rot. So err on the
      side of caution and avoid overwatering them.</p>
      <p>Some pro tips to avoid overwatering the roots:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use a few ice cubes to slowly release water into the soil.</li>
        <li>Use a spray bottle to water the succulent</li>
      </ul>
